      "description": "A monumental adventure set in the 16th century, based on the novel by Nikolai Gogol Cossack leader Taras Bulba ( Yul Brynner ) goes to war against his former Polish comrades. In the fight against the traitors, his son Andrei ( Tony Curtis ) falls in love with the beautiful Polish woman Natalia ( Christine Kaufmann ). Out of love for her, he even switches sides. The Oscar-nominated score by Franz Waxman is as brilliant as the battles filmed in Argentina.",
